  <title translate="true">Acceleration</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword translate="true">Motion Definition:<keyword translate="true">Acceleration</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="" style="text-align:left; text-indent:0px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.00; background-color:transparent; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; border:none; tabstops:none;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1" style="width:450px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Acceleration</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">: the rate-of-change of </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-POP-Velocity" styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Velocity</link><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> with respect to time.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;"/></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small" translate="true">Notes</text><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">: If you increase the speed of a machine by 2×, the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-POP-Acceleration-Nominal" styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">nominal acceleration</link><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> increases by 4×. Machine components must reach 2× the velocity in 0.5× the time.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MT-Motion-Cam-Laws" styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true">Traditional Motion-Laws</link><text styleclass="Popup Box" translate="true"> are frequently named with reference to the shape of the acceleration profile. E.g. Modified Trapezoidal.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
